
Preheat oven to 350 F and grease a 9" x 13" pan or two 9" round pans.

Beat 2 c granulated sugar, 1 1/4 c oil, 4 eggs, and 2 tsp vanilla together in a
large bowl unil well combined. Mix in 2 c flour, 2 tsp baking soda, 2 tsp 
baking powder, 2 tsp cinnamon, and 1/2 tsp salt. Stir in 3 c grated carrots. 
Pour into the prepared pan(s).

Bake until a toothpick inserted in the middle of the cake comes out clean, 
about 40 minutes. Let cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then turn onto a wire 
rack and cool completely.

Beat 4 oz butter, 8 oz cream cheese, 4 c confectioners' sugar, and 1 tsp 
vanilla in a large bowl until smooth and creamy. Frost the cake once it's 
completely cooled.


Ingredients: 
2 c granulated sugar
1 1/4 c vegetable oil
4 eggs
3 tsp vanilla extract
2 c all-purpose flour
2 tsp baking soda
2 tsp baking powder
2 tsp ground cinnamon
1/2 tsp salt
3 c grated carrots
4 oz butter, softened
8 oz cream cheese, softened
4 c confectioners' sugar
